==English==
===Etymology===
Latin ''[[refutare]]''

===Pronunciation===
American ([[SAMPA]]): [r@"fjut]

===Transitive verb===
'''to refute''' (''[[present participle]]'' '''refuting''', ''[[past tense]] and [[past participle]]'' '''refuted''')

#To [[prove]] (something) to be [[false]] or [[incorrect]].
#(''non-standard'') To [[deny]] the [[truth]] or [[correctness]] of (something).

====Usage note====
*The accepted meaning of this word is "to prove false".  The meaning "to deny" is non-standard and is avoided by careful speakers and writers.
